HEADWORD: Suboxide
<hw>Sub*ox"ide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>An oxide containing a relatively small amount of oxygen, and less
than the normal proportion; <as>as, potassium <ex>suboxide</ex>,
<chform>K4O</chform></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subpeduncular</ent>⟦br⟧
